The paper discusses security challenges in Software-Defined Networking (SDN), which is a subfield of computer networking (cs.NI) and security (cs.CR). The proposed solution involves decentralization and authentication, which are also relevant to distributed systems (cs.Distributed Systems). The paper also mentions programmable network configuration and access control, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE) and data centers (cs.DC).
